{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, our results show that working with authentic tools that allow for solving \"real-world problems\" poses a lot of challenges for students and teachers alike.",
    "Similar to other areas of computing education, this raises the question of design principles for adequate tool support that foster students' creativity and agency.",
    "The next step in the first action research cycle is to discuss these difficulties with the participating teachers in order to co-design strategies and approaches to address them for the second cycle.",
    "In this way, the results of our study contribute to the identification of learning difficulties in K-12 classrooms and provide valuable insights for improving AI education on an empirical basis -laying the foundation for empowering students to shape their future.",
    "Critical, ethical, empowering design of AI/ML systems for social good"
  ]
}